<misra_rule>
MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.1 is: A project shall not contain unreachable code.

</misra_rule>
<response format>
Provide your answer with these fields.
- is_rule_violated: whether the rule is violated or not (true/false),
- scenario: a specific violation scenario.
</response format>
<target_code>
Here is the code of MHD_fini:
```c
void
MHD_fini (void)
{
#ifdef HTTPS_SUPPORT
  gnutls_global_deinit ();
#endif /* HTTPS_SUPPORT */
#if defined(MHD_WINSOCK_SOCKETS)
  WSACleanup ();
#endif /* MHD_WINSOCK_SOCKETS */
  MHD_monotonic_sec_counter_finish ();
}
```
</target_code>
<target_code>
Here is the code fragment that you need to analyze:
```c
#ifdef HTTPS_SUPPORT
  gnutls_global_deinit ();
#endif /* HTTPS_SUPPORT */
```
Focus on the above code fragment and judge whether it violates the rule 2.1 or not.
</target_code>
scenario: The call to gnutls_global_deinit() is conditionally compiled under #ifdef HTTPS_SUPPORT. This is not intrinsically unreachable: if HTTPS_SUPPORT can be defined in some build configuration the call is reachable. A rule violation would occur only if HTTPS_SUPPORT is guaranteed never to be defined in any project configuration (so the call can never be compiled into or executed in any build), in which case the code is effectively unreachable across the project.
